Vice President Kamala Harris convened a meeting at the White House with medical experts and reproductive rights leaders to discuss protecting reproductive health care. The participants focused on access to medication abortion, which is currently facing legal challenges and accounts for over half of all abortions in the United States. They also discussed the impact of the Supreme Court's decision to overturn Roe v. Wade and the difficulties in accessing care due to attacks on medication abortion. The participants emphasized the safety and efficacy of medication abortion and the need to safeguard access to this critical medication. They also discussed the chilling effect of state abortion restrictions on healthcare providers. The Vice President highlighted how attempts to undermine access to medication abortion threaten both the public health system and fundamental freedoms. The participants also talked about the importance of coalition building in the fight for reproductive freedom. The Vice President thanked them for their dedication to providing reproductive care and their leadership in protecting the ability for people to make decisions about their own bodies.